label: Book of hours (Dutch), BPL 3073

metadata.label: Content
metadata.value: Contains: (ff. 1r-49v) Hours of the Virgin. - (ff. 50r-76r) Hours of Eternal Wisdom. - (ff. 76r-102r) Long Hours of the Cross. - (ff. 102r-108r) Short Hours of the Cross. - (ff. 109r-131r) Hours of the Holy Spirit. - (ff. 131r-154r) Seven psalms with litany. - (ff. 154v-190v) Office of the Dead. - (ff. 191r-193r) Prayers. - Contains no calendar.

metadata.label: Note
value: Illumination: At the beginning of the Hours large initials, raised in gold and with painted border, partly floral motifs, partly historiated: Virgin with Child (1r), Man of Sorrows (76v), Holy Face of Jesus (102r); simple penwork on f. 191r. Initials alternating in red and blue; at the canonical hours sometimes painted initials, gold-framed and with border decoration.
Two leaves missing after f. 167. Several leaves in disorder (ff. 9r/10v and 85v/86v) possibly with loss of text; some leaves cropped.

Binding: Medieval binding, contemporary. - Leather (brown goatskin, blind-tooled) over wooden boards. Decorated with panel stamp on both sides (John the Baptist with lamb; described by Verheyden 1933). Two clasp fastenings (closing back to front, renewed). - Bookblock resewn, spine renewed..
Also described by BNM, MMDC and A.W. Byvanckgenootschap (database RKD, The Hague).
Bought at the auction held by Sotheby's, London, in 1984 (cat. nr. 58).
